## What Changed

Closeout Step 6 previously said "write a final track point (phase: review)" without specifying the
required fields. Wakeup Step 3b checks the last line of the previous session's track for
`completed == true or event == "closeout"` to determine CLEAN vs INTERRUPTED. Because Step 6 never
wrote those fields, **every session woke up as INTERRUPTED** even after a successful, complete
closeout.

Discovered in session-20260405-0012 (Minder) when comparing the closeout Step 6 instructions
against the Step 3b integrity check condition.

## Why It Matters

Every spoke running the current closeout protocol will show INTERRUPTED at next wakeup, regardless
of whether the session ended cleanly. This causes false recovery prompts (Green Light / Red Light)
at every session start, creates noise, and erodes trust in the integrity check.

## Fix

Update closeout Step 6 to write a terminal track entry with both required fields:

```json
{"event": "closeout", "completed": true, "session_id": "{session_id}", "ts": "{ISO-8601}", "phase": "review", "session_number": N}
```

## Migration Instructions

In each spoke's `wai-closeout.md` (typically `.claude/commands/wai-closeout.md`), find Step 6 and
replace the vague "write a final track point" instruction with the specific terminal entry format:

```markdown
### 6. Finalize Session Track

Write a final track point as the **terminal entry** — this is the marker wakeup Step 3b uses to
detect a clean session. The entry MUST include both `event: "closeout"` and `completed: true`:

\`\`\`json
{"event": "closeout", "completed": true, "session_id": "{session_id}", "ts": "{ISO-8601}", "phase": "review", "session_number": N}
\`\`\`

Do NOT delete the track file — it's the permanent session record. A session without this terminal
entry will show as INTERRUPTED on next wakeup.
```

Also update the framework template at `templates/commands/wai-closeout.md` if it exists.

## Prerequisites

```bash
# Verify the current closeout Step 6 text in spoke
grep -A3 "### 6\." .claude/commands/wai-closeout.md | head -5
```

